is.nan.data.frame <- function(x)
  do.call(cbind, lapply(x, is.nan))

cases<-read.table("~/OneDrive - UWM/Normalization paper Sept 2020/Data/sewershed_cases_bydate_uwm.csv", sep = ",", h=T)
cases$SpecCollectedDate<-format(as.Date(as.character(cases$SpecCollectedDate), format="%m/%d/%y"), "%m/%d/%Y")
cases <- cases %>%
  arrange(desc(as.factor(City))) %>% 
  group_by(as.factor(City)) %>% 
  mutate(case_rate7day = zoo::rollmean(case_rate, k = 7, fill = NA)) %>% 
  dplyr::ungroup()
cases<-as.data.frame(cases)

Data per filter => assay variability

data.per.filter<-data %>%
  group_by(Sample_ID, City, CV, Collection_Date_Start) %>%
  summarize(N1.avg = mean(N1_avg, na.rm=TRUE),
            #N1c.avg = mean(N1_avg_censored, na.rm=TRUE),
            N1.LevelDetection = sum(ifelse(N1_LevelDetection=="Quantifiable", 100, ifelse(N1_LevelDetection=="BLQ", 1,0)), na.rm=TRUE),
            N1.count = sum(!is.na(N1_LevelDetection)),
            N1.LOD = mean(N1_LOD, na.rm=TRUE),

            N2.avg = mean(N2_avg, na.rm=TRUE),
            #N2c.avg = mean(N2_avg_censored, na.rm=TRUE),
            N2.LevelDetection = sum(ifelse(N2_LevelDetection=="Quantifiable", 100, ifelse(N2_LevelDetection=="BLQ", 1,0)), na.rm=TRUE),
            N2.count = sum(!is.na(N2_LevelDetection)),
            N2.LOD = mean(N2_LOD, na.rm=TRUE),
            
            BCoV.avg = mean(BCoV, na.rm=TRUE), ###added from here recovery controls in data per filter###
            PMMoV.avg = mean(PMMoV, na.rm=TRUE),
            HF183.avg = mean(HF183, na.rm=TRUE),
            TSS = mean (TSS..mg.L.,na.rm = TRUE),
            Flow = mean(Daily.Avg.Flow..MGD., na.rm = TRUE),
            .groups = 'drop')

data.per.filter<-as.data.frame(data.per.filter)
data.per.filter.NaN<-is.nan.data.frame(data.per.filter)
data.per.filter[data.per.filter.NaN]<-NA
names(data.per.filter)<-sub("[.]", "_", names(data.per.filter))

data.per.filter$N1_LevelDetection<-ifelse(data.per.filter$N1_LevelDetection>=100, "Quantifiable", ifelse(data.per.filter$N1_LevelDetection>0, "BLQ", "BLD"))
data.per.filter$N2_LevelDetection<-ifelse(data.per.filter$N2_LevelDetection>=100, "Quantifiable", ifelse(data.per.filter$N2_LevelDetection>0, "BLQ", "BLD"))

Data per day (average performed the average per filter) => filter (+assay) variability

data.per.day<-data.per.filter %>%
  group_by(CV, City, Collection_Date_Start) %>%
  summarize(N1.avg.day = mean(N1_avg, na.rm=TRUE), 
            N1.LevelDetection.day = sum(ifelse(N1_LevelDetection=="Quantifiable", 100, ifelse(N1_LevelDetection=="BLQ", 1,0)), na.rm=TRUE),
            N1.count.day = sum(!is.na(N1_LevelDetection)),
            N1.LOD.day = mean(N1_LOD, na.rm=TRUE),
            
            N2.avg.day = mean(N2_avg, na.rm=TRUE),
            N2.LevelDetection.day = sum(ifelse(N2_LevelDetection=="Quantifiable", 100, ifelse(N2_LevelDetection=="BLQ", 1,0)), na.rm=TRUE),
            N2.count.day = sum(!is.na(N2_LevelDetection)),
            N2.LOD.day = mean(N2_LOD, na.rm=TRUE),

            N1N2.avg.day = mean(c(N1_avg, N2_avg), na.rm=TRUE),

            BCoV.avg.day = mean(BCoV_avg, na.rm=TRUE),
            BCoV.rsd.day = sd(BCoV_avg, na.rm=TRUE)/mean(BCoV_avg, na.rm=TRUE),

            PMMoV.avg.day = mean(PMMoV_avg, na.rm=TRUE),
            PMMoV.rsd.day = sd(PMMoV_avg, na.rm=TRUE)/mean(PMMoV_avg, na.rm=TRUE),

            HF183.avg.day = mean(HF183_avg, na.rm=TRUE),
            HF183.rsd.day = sd(HF183_avg, na.rm=TRUE)/mean(HF183_avg, na.rm=TRUE),

            TSS.day = mean(TSS, na.rm=TRUE),
            Flow.day = mean(Flow, na.rm=TRUE),
            .groups = 'drop')

data.per.day<-as.data.frame(data.per.day)
data.per.day.NaN<-is.nan.data.frame(data.per.day)
data.per.day[data.per.day.NaN]<-NA
names(data.per.day)<-sub("[.]", "_", names(data.per.day)); names(data.per.day)<-sub("[.]", "_", names(data.per.day))

data.per.day$N1_LevelDetection_day<-ifelse(data.per.day$N1_LevelDetection_day>=100, "Quantifiable", ifelse(data.per.day$N1_LevelDetection_day>0, "BLQ", "BLD"))
data.per.day$N2_LevelDetection_day<-ifelse(data.per.day$N2_LevelDetection_day>=100, "Quantifiable", ifelse(data.per.day$N2_LevelDetection_day>0, "BLQ", "BLD"))
data.per.day$N1N2_LevelDetection_day<-ifelse(data.per.day$N1_LevelDetection_day=="Quantifiable" | data.per.day$N2_LevelDetection_day=="Quantifiable", "Quantifiable", 
                                             ifelse(data.per.day$N1_LevelDetection_day=="BLQ" | data.per.day$N2_LevelDetection_day=="BLQ", "BLQ", "BLD"))

data.per.day$N1_censored_DHS<-ifelse(data.per.day$N1_LevelDetection_day=="BLD", data.per.day$N1_LOD_day/2,  data.per.day$N1_avg_day)
data.per.day$N2_censored_DHS<-ifelse(data.per.day$N2_LevelDetection_day=="BLD", data.per.day$N2_LOD_day/2,  data.per.day$N2_avg_day)
data.per.day$N1N2_censored_DHS<-ifelse(data.per.day$N1_LevelDetection_day=="BLD" & data.per.day$N2_LevelDetection_day=="BLD", ((data.per.day$N1_LOD_day/2)+(data.per.day$N2_LOD_day/2))/2,  data.per.day$N1N2_avg_day)

Shuchens plot - preparation (Figures 3 & 4)

shuchen.plot<-melt(data.per.day.cases, id.vars = c("CV", "City", "Collection_Date_Start", "N1N2_LevelDetection_day"), measure.vars = c("N1_censored_DHS",   "N2_censored_DHS",  "N1N2_censored_DHS", "PMMoV_avg_day", "HF183_avg_day", "BCoV_avg_day", "case_rate7day"))
## Warning in melt(data.per.day.cases, id.vars = c("CV", "City",
## "Collection_Date_Start", : The melt generic in data.table has been passed
## a data.frame and will attempt to redirect to the relevant reshape2 method;
## please note that reshape2 is deprecated, and this redirection is now
## deprecated as well. To continue using melt methods from reshape2 while both
## libraries are attached, e.g. melt.list, you can prepend the namespace like
## reshape2::melt(data.per.day.cases). In the next version, this warning will
## become an error.
names(shuchen.plot)[5]<-"assays"
shuchen.plot$assays<-plyr::revalue(shuchen.plot$assays, c("N1_censored_DHS"="N1", "N2_censored_DHS"="N2", "N1N2_censored_DHS"="N1/N2", "PMMoV_avg_day"="PMMoV", "HF183_avg_day"="HF183", "BCoV_avg_day"="BCoV", "case_rate7day"="Case rate"))
shuchen.plot$assays <- ordered(shuchen.plot$assays, levels = c("HF183", "PMMoV", "N1/N2", "N1", "N2", "BCoV", "Case rate"))
shuchen.plot$City <- ordered(shuchen.plot$City, levels = c("Village of Grafton", "Port Washington", "Cedarburg", "Burlington", "South Milwaukee", "Green Bay_DP", "Brookfield", "Waukesha", "Racine", "Green Bay_PLT", "Milwaukee_JI", "Milwaukee_SS"))
shuchen.plot$City <- plyr::revalue(shuchen.plot$City, c("Village of Grafton"="Grafton", "Port Washington"="Port Washington", "Cedarburg"="Cedarburg", "Burlington"="Burlington", "South Milwaukee"="South Milwaukee", "Green Bay_DP"="Green Bay DP", "Brookfield"="Brookfield", "Waukesha"="Waukesha", "Racine"="Racine", "Green Bay_PLT"="Green Bay PLT", "Milwaukee_JI"="Milwaukee JI", "Milwaukee_SS"="Milwaukee SS"))
shuchen.plot<-subset(shuchen.plot, value!="NA" & value!="NaN")

## Warning: Removed 1 rows containing missing values (geom_bar).

Figure 4 (CDC-censored data) 8.13*3.83

max.cases<-max(subset(shuchen.plot, assays=="Case rate")[,c(6)], na.rm = TRUE)
max.factor<-max(subset(shuchen.plot, assays=="N1/N2")[,c(6)], na.rm = TRUE)
factor.correction<-max.factor/max.cases
shuchen.plot.1<-subset(shuchen.plot, City %in% c("Grafton", "Port Washington", "Cedarburg", "Burlington", "South Milwaukee", "Green Bay DP"))
main.panel<-ggplot(subset(shuchen.plot.1, assays=="N1/N2") , aes(x=Collection_Date_Start, y=value, group=assays)) +
  geom_point(aes(color=assays, shape=N1N2_LevelDetection_day)) +
  scale_color_manual(values=c("#d1495b")) +
  scale_shape_manual(values=c(2,1,16)) +
  ylim(0,160000) +
  labs(x = "Date", y = "SARS-CoV-2 wastewater concentration (cp/L)") +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = function(x) format(x, scientific = TRUE)) +
  facet_grid(. ~ City, scales = "free_x", space = "free_x") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5), panel.border = element_blank(),panel.background = element_rect(fill = "white", colour = "black"), panel.grid.major = element_blank(), panel.grid.minor = element_blank(), legend.position="none") + 
    scale_x_date(date_breaks = "1 month", date_minor_breaks = "1 month", labels = NULL) +
xlab(NULL)
## Scale for 'y' is already present. Adding another scale for 'y', which will
## replace the existing scale.
main.panel <- main.panel + geom_line(data=subset(shuchen.plot.1,  assays=="Case rate"), aes(x=Collection_Date_Start, y=value*factor.correction)) + 
  scale_y_continuous(sec.axis = sec_axis(~ . /factor.correction, name = "Case rate per 100,000 people"))
